<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM3.6.10">
<l>maiyilaṅku karuṅkuvaḷai maruṅkalarum vayalāli</l>
<l>neyyilaṅku cuṭarāḻip paṭaiyāṉai neṭumālai</l>
<l>kaiyilaṅku vēlkaliyaṉ kaṇṭuraitta tamiḻmālai</l>
<l>yaiyiraṇṭu mivaivallārk karuviṉaika ḷaṭaiyāvē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>For those who master these twice-five [verses of] the Tamil garland</l>
<l>Composed and spoken by Kaliyaṉ, a spear which glistens [in his] hand,</l>
<l rend="indent">about tall Māl,</l>
<l>The one whose weapon is the fiery discus which glistens with blood,</l>
<l>In Āli, its paddy fields blossoming on [all] sides with dark lilies</l>
<l rend="indent">which glisten [like] kohl, harsh deeds will not adhere.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
